In this case, the dot product is
$$(3)(-5) + (-4)(2) + (-3)(1) = -15 - 8 - 3 = -26.$$
Final Answer: $\boxed{-26}$ I hope it is correct.
ground_truth:
The dot product of $\begin{pmatrix} 3 \\ -4 \\ -3 \end{pmatrix}$ and $\begin{pmatrix} -5 \\ 2 \\ 1 \end{pmatrix}$ is
